Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf=20wave=2018=20patch=200086=20=E2=80=94=20d?=
 =?UTF-8?q?irect-VESA=20hot=20path=20(env-gated,=20default=20OFF)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DOS-PORT (patch 0086, Phase 9 wave 18). Hypothesis: bypassing
SDL_RenderPresent + SDL_UpdateWindowSurface and writing the engine's
window surface directly into VRAM via SDL/0034's PresentFull helper
saves the SDL3-state-machine cost on every flip. Wave-16-3's WAVE16-FB-
FIRSTFLUSH diagnostic measured present=5ms on real HW at 8bpp; that's
~13% of the 38.7 ms/flip budget at 25.6 fps wave-17.6 baseline.

Predicted +2-5 fps title (framed as a hypothesis to measure per
memory/perf_predictions_unreliable.md, not a goal to defend).
Possible outcomes:
  +5 fps -> follow-up patch promotes to default-ON
  +0 fps -> SDL layer wasn't the bottleneck; close wave 18, pivot
            to wave 19 (Cirrus hwblit) with confidence
  visual artifacts -> revert; risks R1/R2/R3 (per prep doc) manifested

API surface consumed (from SDL/0034 sdl-engine deliverable):
  SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState  — snapshot fb_state into POD struct
  SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration — cheap mode-change detection
  SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull   — single-call full-frame flush; picks
                                   LFB memcpy / banked dosmemput / multi-
                                   bank flush automatically
  SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette — VGA DAC sync on master-palette change

Integration in Renderer.cpp::flip():
  1. Gate on SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRECT_VESA=1 (strict-1 match per
     wave-16+ default-OFF / strict-1-to-enable convention; matches
     SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB / DISPLAY_START_FIX / LFB_SENTINEL /
     PREVFRAME_DIFF).
  2. Skip first DIRTY_FIRST_N_FRAMES (init backbuffer undefined) and
     any flip with _force_full_refresh set (flushAll, scene reset).
  3. _direct_vesa_present():
     - SDL_FlushRenderer to drain SW-renderer queue (R1 — SW renderer
       dst IS the window surface; flush=copy is sufficient without
       SDL_RenderPresent's page-flip semantics)
     - SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration / GetState on first call /
       generation bump
     - SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette on master_palette->version drift
     - SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull single-call full-frame present
  4. On any false return (state invalid, dim mismatch, pitches differ,
     PresentFull failed) fall through to existing SDL path. No visual
     regression even if direct path never engages.

R2 (window-surface re-allocation drift between flips) is covered by
SDL/0034 v2's generation counter — populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb
bumps it on window-create AND lazy-reinit, so a generation bump
signals BOTH "fb_state changed" AND "window->surface->pixels may have
moved." Re-snapshotting on bump is the canonical mitigation; no
separate SDL_RenderPresent heartbeat is required (see SDL/0034
header § Mode-change semantics).

Diagnostic counters bumped per attempt and reported in the per-100-flip
phase-timing audit block (extends the existing log line):
  [direct-vesa: presents=N total_ms=M avg_ms_x10=X failed=N]
  [ablation: ... DIRECT_VESA=<0|1>]

Initial DEBUG.LOG announce on initVideo and one-shot snapshot log on
first eligible flip ("direct-vesa: snapshot @gen=...") so each iter's
configuration is greppable from DEBUG.LOG.

Test plan (subsequent tasks #4-#6):
  - DOSBox-X visual A/B with both polarities (off=zero-change baseline,
    on=engaged path)
  - Real-HW iter: three runs in one boot via DOS REN — OFF baseline,
    ON banked, ON+SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB=1
  - Logback analysis reports measured fps vs wave-17.6 baseline (25.6),
    vs prediction (+2-5), vs 50 fps KPI

Documentation: docs/BOOT.md updated under Diagnostic / development
options per memory/env_vars_document_in_user_docs.md convention.

References:
  docs/PHASE9-WAVE-17-18-PLAN.md § 4
  /tmp/wave18-nxengine-prep.md (prep doc with R1/R2/R3 risk analysis)
  /tmp/wave18-sdl-flush-audit.md (sdl-engine SDL_dosframebuffer.c audit)
  vendor/SDL/include/SDL3/SDL_dosvesa_directaccess.h (SDL/0034 API doc)

